obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (41255)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 14th May, 1951, vide Notification No. F. 40-5/50-G, 3 dated the 10th May, 1951, Gazette of India, 1951, Part I. sec. 1.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41255&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Visva-Bharati Act, 1951.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (41256)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration of Visva-Bharati as an institution of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 60 of 1961, s. 2 (w.e.f. 19-12-1961).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41256&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `Whereas the late`
  line `Rabindranath Tagore (Thakur) founded an institution known as Visva-Bharati at Santiniketan in the`
  line `district of Birbhum in West Bengal the objects of which are such as to make the institution one of national`
  line `importance, it is hereby declared that the institution known as "Visva-Bharati" aforesaid is an institution`
  line `of national importance ^1[and is as such hereby constituted as a University].`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (41257)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 3, for section 3 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41257&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Definitions.--In this Act, and in all Statutes made hereunder, unless the context otherwise`
  line requires,--
  line
  line `(a) "academic staff" means such categories of staff as are designated as academic staff by the`
  line statutes;
  line
  line `(b) "Acharya (Chancellor)" and "Upacharya (Vice- Chancellor)" mean, respectively, the Acharya`
  line `(Chancellor) and the Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor) of the University;`
  line
  line `(c) "adhyapaka" includes a Professor, Reader, Lecturer and any other person engaged in`
  line `imparting instruction in relation to any learning process and designated as an adhyapaka by the`
  line Ordinances;
  line
  line `(d) "Alumni Association" means the Association of the Alumni of the University, constituted`
  line `under the provisions of this Act and the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(e) "approved institution" means an institution (not being an institution maintained by the`
  line `University) of higher learning or studies approved by the University;`
  line
  line `(f) "Bhavana" means an academic institution maintained by the University and named as such;`
  line
  line `(g) "campus" means a unit established or constituted by the University for imparting instruction`
  line `or supervising research, or both;`
  line
  line `(h) "Chatravaso" means a unit of residence, or of corporate life, for the students of the University`
  line `provided, maintained or recognised by the University;`
  line
  line `(i) "Department" means a Department of Studies and includes a centre of studies established by,`
  line `or under, the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(j) "employee of the University" means any person appointed by the University or any Institution,`
  line `and includes an employee of a Bhavana;`
  line
  line `(k) "Institute Board" means a Board constituted by the University for the management of an`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(l) "Institution" means an institution maintained by the University;`
  line
  line `(m) "Karma-Samiti (Executive Council)" means the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) of the`
  line University;
  line
  line `(n) "Patha-Samiti (Board of Studies)" means a Board constituted by the University for the`
  line `regulation of studies;`
  line
  line `(o) "prescribed" means prescribed by the Statutes, Ordinances or Regulations;`
  line
  line `(p) "Samsad (Court)" means the Samsad (Court) of the University;`
  line
  line `(q) "Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council)" means the Siksha-Samiti (Academic council) of the`
  line University;
  line
  line `(r) "Statutes", "Ordinances" and "Regulations" mean, respectively, such Statutes, Ordinances and`
  line `Regulations of the University as are for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(s) "University" means the institution known as Visva- Bharati and incorporated as a University`
  line `under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (41258)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Incorporation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 60 of 1961, s. 4 (w.e.f. 19-12-1961).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41258&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The first Acharya (Chancellor) and Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor) of the`
  line `University who shall be the persons appointed in this behalf by the Central Government by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, and the first members of the Samsad (Court) and all persons, who may hereafter`
  line `become or be appointed as such officers or members, so long as they continue to hold such office or`
  line `membership, are hereby constituted a body corporate ^1[as a unitary, teaching and residential University]`
  line `by the name of Visva-Bharati, and shall have perpetual succession and a common seal, and shall sue and`
  line `be sued by that name.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (41259)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Effect of incorporation of the University in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 19-12-1961).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41259&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On and from the commencement of`
  line `this Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) all references in any enactment to the Society of the name of Visva-Bharati registered on the`
  line `16th May, 1922, under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860), shall be construed as`
  line `references to the University;`
  line
  line `^1[(ii) all property, assets, rights and liabilities of the said Society shall be the property, assets,`
  line `rights and liabilities of the University and any will, deed or other document, whether made or`
  line `executed before or after the commencement of this Act, which contains or purports to contain any`
  line `bequest, gift, trust, payment of money or transfer or assignment of any right or property, movable or`
  line `immovable, in favour of the said Society shall be construed as if the University was therein named`
  line `instead of the said Society;]`
  line
  line `(iii) subject to the provisions of this Act, every person employed immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act in the said Society shall hold employment in the University by the same`
  line `tenure and upon the same terms and conditions and with the same rights and privileges as to pension`
  line `and gratuity as he would have held under the said Society, if this Act had not been passed:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the University decides to alter the terms and conditions of service of any such`
  line `employee, a fresh contract shall be executed for the purpose, and if the employee is not agreeable to serve`
  line `under the new terms and conditions, his services may be terminated in accordance with his original`
  line `contract of employment or, if no provision is made therein in this behalf, on payment to him by way of`
  line `compensation of an amount equal to his salary for six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (41260)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `The objects of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 4 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41260&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. The objects of the University.--(1) The objects of the University shall be to disseminate and`
  line `advance knowledge and understanding by providing instructional, extension and research facilities and by`
  line `the example and influence of its corporate life, and the University shall, in organising its activities, have`
  line `due regard to the following objects for which the Visva-Bharati at Santiniketan was founded by`
  line `Rabindranath Tagore, as expressed in his own words, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) to study the mind of Man in its realisation of different aspects of truth from diverse points of view;`
  line
  line `(ii) to bring into more intimate relations with one another, through patient study and research, the`
  line `different cultures of the East on the basis of their underlying unity;`
  line
  line `(iii) to approach the West from the standpoint of such a unity of the life and thought of Asia;`
  line
  line `(iv) to seek to realise in a common fellowship of study the meeting of the East and the West, and`
  line `thus ultimately to strengthen the fundamental conditions of world peace through the establishment of`
  line `free communication of ideas between the two hemispheres; and`
  line
  line `(v) with such ideals in view to provide at Santiniketan aforesaid a Centre of Culture where`
  line `research into and study of the religion, literature, history, science and art of Hindu, Buddhist, Jain,`
  line `Islamic, Sikh, Christian and other civilisations may be pursued along with the culture of the West,`
  line `with that simplicity in externals which is necessary for true spiritual realisation in amity, good`
  line `fellowship and co-operation between the thinkers and scholars of both Eastern and Western countries,`
  line `free from all antagonisms of race, nationality, creed or caste and in the name of the One Supreme`
  line `Being who is Shantam, Shivam, Advaitam.`
  line
  line `(2) The objects of the University shall also include harmonising the cultures of India, the East and the`
  line `West by, among other things, the admission of students and appointment of adhyapakas from various`
  line `regions of India and various countries of the world, and by providing incentives therefor.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_b:
  sectionId (41261)
  sectionNo 5B
  orderNo 7
  title `Principles to be followed in organising activities of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 4 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41261&sectionno=5B&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[5B. Principles to be followed in organising activities of the University.--The University shall, in`
  line `organising its activities and the implementation of its academic programmes, have due regard to the`
  line `pattern of education envisaged by Rabindranath Tagore in his writings.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (41262)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 8
  title `Powers of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 5, for section 6 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41262&sectionno=6&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Powers of the University.--The University shall have the following powers, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) to provide facilities for studies, instruction, socially useful productive work and community`
  line `service and research in such branches of learning as may be deemed desirable and found practicable`
  line `by the University and for the promotion of understanding of cultures between the East and the West`
  line `and for the advancement of learning and dissemination of knowledge generally;`
  line
  line `(2) to undertake educational experiments and evolve contents, systems and methods of education`
  line `for the furtherance of the objects of the University;`
  line
  line `(3) to make provision for research and advisory services; and for that purpose, to enter into such`
  line `arrangements with other institutions or bodies as the University may deem necessary;`
  line
  line `(4) to co-operate, collaborate or associate with any other University, authority or institution of`
  line `learning in such manner and for such purposes as the University may determine;`
  line
  line `(5) to approve any institution of higher learning or studies for such purposes as the University`
  line `may determine, and to withdraw such approval;`
  line
  line `(6) to establish and maintain such Bhavanas, Schools of Studies and Research, Chatravasas,`
  line `Gymnasia and such other institutions as are deemed necessary, from time to time, for the`
  line `development of a healthy corporate life in the University and to abolish any such Bhavana, School,`
  line `Chatravasa, Gymnasium or other institution;`
  line
  line `(7) to establish, at any place in India, campuses, special centres, specialised laboratories or other`
  line `units for research and instruction as are, in the opinion of the University, necessary for the furtherance`
  line `of its objects;`
  line
  line `(8) to organise the application of class room, library and laboratory learning to problems of the`
  line `villages as part of the curriculum;`
  line
  line `(9) to undertake the promotion of adult education, rural re-construction, co-operative`
  line `organisations, social welfare, development of cottage industries and all other nation-building`
  line `activities and works for the benefit of the public;`
  line
  line `(10) to establish such examination centres and to recognise such certificates as may be necessary`
  line `to give effect to the provisions of section 7A;`
  line
  line `(11) to grant, subject to such conditions as the University may determine, diplomas or certificates`
  line `to, and confer degrees or other academic distinctions (on the basis of examinations, evaluation or`
  line `other modes of testing) on, persons;`
  line
  line `(12) to confer honorary degrees or other distinctions in the manner prescribed by the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(13) to determine the standards for admission and the methods of admission to courses of the`
  line `University, which methods shall include examinations, evaluation and other modes of testing;`
  line
  line `(14) to supervise the residences of students of the University and to make arrangements for`
  line `promoting their health and general welfare;`
  line
  line `(15) to make such special arrangements in respect of women students as the University may`
  line `consider desirable;`
  line
  line `(16) to regulate the conduct of students of the University, and to take such disciplinary measures`
  line `in this regard as may be deemed necessary;`
  line
  line `(17) to create such teaching and other academic posts as may be required by the University and to`
  line `appoint persons to such posts;`
  line
  line `(18) to appoint Visiting Professors, Emeritus Professors, Fellows, Scholars, Resident Artists,`
  line `Resident Writers or such other persons who may contribute to the achievement of the objects of the`
  line University;
  line
  line `(19) to appoint or recognise persons as Professors, Readers or Lecturers or otherwise as`
  line `adhyapakas of the University;`
  line
  line `(20) to approve persons working in--`
  line
  line `(a) any institution co-operating, collaborating or associating with the University; or`
  line
  line `(b) any approved institution,`
  line
  line `for imparting instruction or supervising research, or both, and to withdraw such approval;`
  line
  line `(21) to undertake publication of literary, scientific, educational and scholarly works and books on`
  line `art, aesthetics and other subjects aimed at better understanding of the different cultures of the world`
  line `and furthering thereby the objectives of the University;`
  line
  line `(22) to appoint persons working in any other University, institution or organisation as adhyapakas`
  line `of the University for a specified period;`
  line
  line `(23) to create administrative, ministerial and other posts in the University and to make`
  line `appointments thereto;`
  line
  line `(24) to provide for the terms and conditions of service of employees, whether employed by the`
  line `University or any institution;`
  line
  line `(25) to regulate the conduct and duties of the employees of the University;`
  line
  line `(26) to regulate and enforce discipline among the employees of the University and to take such`
  line `disciplinary measures in this regard as may be deemed necessary;`
  line
  line `(27) to make arrangements for promoting the health and general welfare of the employees of the`
  line University;
  line
  line `(28) to demand and receive payment of fees and other charges;`
  line
  line `(29) to institute and award fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(30) to receive benefactions, donations and gifts, and to acquire, hold, manage and dispose of any`
  line `property, movable or immovable, including trust and endowment properties, for the purposes of the`
  line University;
  line
  line `(31) to borrow, with the approval of the Central Government, whether on the security of the`
  line `property of the University or otherwise, money for the purposes of the University;`
  line
  line `(32) to establish campuses within the territorial limits of the University specified in the Second`
  line Schedule;
  line
  line `(33) to admit students of any other University or College whether in India or outside to any`
  line `examination of the University subject to such conditions as the University may lay down for the`
  line purpose;
  line
  line `(34) to do all such acts and things as may be necessary or incidental to the exercise of all or any`
  line `of the powers of the University or as are necessary or conducive to the attainment of all or any of the`
  line `objects of the University.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (41263)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 9
  title `Territorial jurisdiction of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41263&sectionno=7&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the powers of`
  line `the University conferred by or under this Act shall be restricted to the area specified in the Second`
  line Schedule.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (41264)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 10
  title `Maintenance of examination centres outside territorial limits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 60 of 1961, s. 7 (w.e.f. 19-12-1961).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41264&sectionno=7A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Maintenance of examination centres outside territorial limits.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 7, the University may establish and maintain, at any place in India examination`
  line `centres for home study courses conducted by its Loka Shiksha Samsad (People's Education Council) and`
  line `recognise, for such purposes as may be provided in the Ordinances, the certificates awarded by the said`
  line `Loka Shiksha Samsad (People's Education Council) on the results of examinations conducted by it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (41265)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 11
  title `University to be open to all races, creeds and classes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 2, for "teachers" (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41265&sectionno=8&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The University shall be open to all`
  line `persons irrespective of sex, nationality, race, creed, caste or class, and no test or condition shall be`
  line `imposed as to religious belief or profession in admitting or appointing members, students, ^1[adhyapakas],`
  line `workers, or in any other connection whatsoever, except in respect of any particular benefaction accepted`
  line `by the University of which such test is made a condition by the instrument creating such benefaction:`
  line
  line `Provided that no benefaction shall hereafter be accepted which in the opinion of the authorities of the`
  line `University involves conditions or obligations opposed to the spirit and object of this section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent religious instruction being`
  line `given in any manner approved of by the authorities concerned to those who have given their consent`
  line `thereto by ^1[adhyapakas] duly and properly authorised for that purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (41266)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 12
  title `Teaching at the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41266&sectionno=9&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `All teaching in the University shall be conducted by and in the`
  line `name of the University in accordance with the Statutes and Ordinances made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (41267)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 13
  title `The Paridarsaka (Visitor).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid for section 10 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41267&sectionno=10&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10.The Paridarsaka (Visitor).--(1) The President of India shall be the Paridarsaka (Visitor) of the`
  line University.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4), the Paridarsaka (Visitor) shall have the right`
  line `to cause an inspection to be made, by such person or persons as he may specify, of the University, its`
  line `buildings, laboratories and equipment, and of any Bhavana or other Institution, and also of the`
  line `examinations, teaching and other work conducted or done by the University, Bhavana or other Institution;`
  line `and to cause an inquiry to be made in like manner in respect of any matter connected with the`
  line `administration or finances of the University.`
  line
  line `(3) The Paridarsaka (Visitor) shall give notice to the University of his intention to cause an`
  line `inspection or inquiry to be made and the University shall, on receipt of such notice, have the right to make, within thirty days or such other period as the Paridarsaka (Visitor) may determine, from the date`
  line `of receipt of the notice, such representations to the Paridarsaka (Visitor) as it may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) After considering the representations, if any, made by the University, the Paridarsaka (Visitor)`
  line `may cause to be made such inspection or inquiry as is referred to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) Where any inspection or inquiry has been caused to be made by the Paridarsaka (Visitor), the`
  line `University shall be entitled to appoint a representative who shall have the right to be present and to be`
  line `heard at such inspection or inquiry.`
  line
  line `(6) The Paridarsaka (Visitor) may address the Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor) with reference to the`
  line `results of such inspection or inquiry together with such views and advice with regard to the action to be`
  line `taken thereon as the Paridarsaka (Visitor) may be pleased to offer, and on receipt of the address made by`
  line `the Paridarsaka (Visitor), the Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor) shall communicate forthwith to the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) the results of the inspection or inquiry and the views of the Paridarsaka`
  line `(Visitor) and the advice tendered by him upon the action to be taken thereon.`
  line
  line `(7) The Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall communicate through the Upacharya (ViceChancellor) to the Paridarsaka (Visitor) such action, if any, as it proposes to take or has been taken by it`
  line `upon the results of such inspection or inquiry.`
  line
  line `(8) Where the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) does not, within a reasonable time, take action to`
  line `the satisfaction of the Paridarsaka (Visitor), the Paridarsaka (Visitor) may, after considering any`
  line `explanation furnished or representation made by the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council), issue such`
  line `directions as he may think fit and Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall be bound to comply with such`
  line directions.
  line
  line `(9) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this section, the Paridarsaka (Visitor may, be`
  line `order in writing, annual any proceeding of the University which is not in conformity with this Act, the`
  line `Statutes or the Ordinances:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any such order he shall call upon the University to show cause why such`
  line `an order should not be made and, if any cause is shown within a reasonable time, he shall consider the`
  line same.
  line
  line `(10) The Paridarsaka (Visitor) shall have such other powers as may be specified in the Statutes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (41268)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 14
  title `The Pradhana (Rector).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41268&sectionno=11&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Government of West Bengal shall be the Pradhana (Rector) of the`
  line University.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (41269)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 15
  title `Officers of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 7, for section 12 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41269&sectionno=12&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Officers of the University.--The following shall be the officers of the University, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) The Acharya (Chancellor);`
  line
  line `(2) The Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor);`
  line
  line `(3) The Director of Studies, Educational Innovations and Rural Reconstruction;`
  line
  line `(4) The Director of Culture and Cultural Relations;`
  line
  line `(5) The Director of Physical Education, Sports, National Service and Student Welfare;`
  line
  line `(6) The Karma-Sachiva (Registrar);`
  line
  line `(7) The Vitta-Adhikari (Finance Officer);`
  line
  line `(8) Adhyakshas of Bhavanas; and`
  line
  line `(9) such other officers as may be declared by the Statutes to be officers of the University.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (41270)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 16
  title `The Acharya (Chancellor).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41270&sectionno=13&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Acharya (Chancellor) shall, by virtue of his office, be the`
  line `Head of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) The Acharya (Chancellor) shall be appointed by the Paridarsaka (Visitor) from out of a panel of`
  line `persons prepared and recommended by the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) under sub-section (2A).`
  line
  line `(2A) The Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall prepare and recommend a panel of not less than`
  line `three persons each of whom shall be a person of eminence in the academic or public life of the country,`
  line `and is in the opinion of the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) a fit and proper person to be appointed as`
  line `the Acharya (Chancellor) of the University:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Paridarsaka (Visitor) does not approve of any of the persons specified in the`
  line `panel prepared and recommended by the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council), he may call upon the`
  line `Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) to prepare a fresh panel of persons.`
  line
  line `(2B) The Acharya (Chancellor) shall hold office for a term of three years and shall be eligible for`
  line `re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Acharya (Chancellor) shall, notwithstanding the expiry of the term of his office,`
  line `continue to hold such office until his successor is appointed and has entered upon his office.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Acharya (Chancellor), shall, if present, preside at the Convocation of the University and at`
  line `meetings of the Samsad (Court) ^2[and the Karma Samiti (Executive Council)].`
  line
  line `(4) Every proposal for the conferment of an honorary degree shall be subject to the confirmation of`
  line `the Acharya (Chancellor).`
  line
  line `(5) The Acharya (Chancellor) shall have such other powers as may be conferred on him by this Act or`
  line `the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 8, for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 60 of 1961, s. 8 (w.e.f. 19-12-1961).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (41271)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 17
  title `The Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 9, for section 14 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41271&sectionno=14&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. The Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor).--(1) The Upacharya (Vice- Chancellor) shall be`
  line `appointed by the Paridarsaka (Visitor) in such manner, for such term and on such emoluments and other`
  line `conditions of service as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) The Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor) shall be the principal executive and academic officer of the`
  line `University, and shall exercise general supervision and control over the academic affairs of the University`
  line `and all Bhavanas and other Institutions and give effect to the decisions of all the authorities of the`
  line University.
  line
  line `(3) The Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor) may, if he is of opinion that immediate action is necessary on`
  line `any matter, exercise any power conferred on any authority of the University by or under this Act and shall`
  line `report to such authority the action taken by him on such matter:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the authority concerned is of opinion that such action ought not to have been taken, it`
  line `may refer the matter to the Paridarsaka (Visitor) whose decision thereon shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided further that an employee of the University, who is aggrieved by the action taken by the`
  line `Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor) under this sub-section, shall have the right to appeal against such action to`
  line `the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) within ninety days from the date on which such action is`
  line `communicated to him and thereupon the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) may confirm, modify or`
  line `reverse the action taken by the Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor).`
  line
  line `(4) The Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor) shall exercise such other powers and perform such other`
  line `functions as may be prescribed by the Statutes and the Ordinances.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (41303)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 18
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41303&sectionno=15&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `[The Arthasachiva (Treasurer).]--Omitted by the Visva-Bharati (Amendment) Act, 1984`
  line `(31 of 1984), s. 10 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (41304)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 19
  title `The Karma-Sachiva (Registrar).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 11, for sections 16 and 17 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41304&sectionno=16&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. The Karma-Sachiva (Registrar).--(1) The Karma-Sachiva (Registrar) shall be appointed in`
  line `such manner, and on such emoluments and other conditions of service, as may be prescribed by the`
  line `statutes and the Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(2) The Karma-Sachiva (Registrar) shall have the power to enter into agreements, sign documents and`
  line `authenticate records on behalf of the University and shall exercise such other powers and perform such`
  line `other functions as may be prescribed by the Statutes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (41273)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 20
  title `Other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 11, for sections 16 and 17 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41273&sectionno=17&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Other officers.--(1) All officers of the University, other than the Acharya (Chancellor), the`
  line `Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor) and the Karma-Sachiva (Registrar), shall be appointed in such manner, for`
  line `such term and on such emoluments and other conditions of service as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers and functions of the officers appointed under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (41274)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 21
  title `Authorities of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41274&sectionno=18&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be authorities of the University:--`
  line
  line `(1) the Samsad (Court);`
  line
  line `(2) the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council);`
  line
  line `(3) the Shiksha Samiti (Academic Council); ^1***`
  line
  line `^2[(4) The Artha-Samiti (Finance Committee);`
  line
  line `(5) The Institute Board; and]`
  line
  line `^3[(6)] such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be authorities of the University.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "and" omitted by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (4) re-numbered as clause (6) by s.12, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (41275)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 22
  title `The Samsad (Court).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for sections 19, 20 and 21 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41275&sectionno=19&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[19. The Samsad (Court).--(1) The constitution of the Samsad (Court) and the term or office of its`
  line `members shall be such as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the Samsad (Court) shall have the following powers`
  line `and functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to review, from time to time, the broad policies and programmes of the University, including`
  line `the maintenance of standards and adherence to the objectives of the University and to suggest`
  line `measures for the development and improvement of the University which shall be considered by the`
  line `appropriate authorities of the University;`
  line
  line `(b) to consider and pass resolutions on the annual report and annual accounts of the University`
  line `and the report of its auditors on such accounts;`
  line
  line `(c) to advice the Paridarsaka (Visitor) in respect of any matter which may be referred to it for`
  line `advice; and`
  line
  line `(d) to exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be prescribed by the`
  line Statutes.]
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (41276)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `The Karma-Samiti (Executive Council).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for sections 22 and 23 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41276&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. The Karma-Samiti (Executive Council).--(1) The Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall be`
  line `the principal executive body of the University.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution of the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) and the term of office of its members`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall exercise the following powers and perform the`
  line `following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to manage and administer the revenue and property of the University and to conduct all`
  line `administrative affairs of the University not otherwise provided for in this act or the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(b) to create teaching and academic posts and to define the duties and conditions of service of`
  line `Professor, Readers, Lecturers and other adhyapakas and academic staff employed by the University:`
  line
  line `Provided that before determining the number, qualifications and emoluments of adhyapakas and`
  line `other academic staff, the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall consider the recommendations of`
  line `the Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council);`
  line
  line `(c) to appoint such Professors, readers, Lecturers and other adhyapakas and academic staff as`
  line `may be necessary on the recommendation of the Selection Committees constituted for the purpose`
  line `and to fill up temporary vacancies therein;`
  line
  line `(d) to provide for the appointment of Visiting Professors, Emeritus Professors, Fellows, Scholars,`
  line `Resident Artists and Resident Writers and to determine the terms and conditions of such appointment;`
  line
  line `(e) to manage and regulate the finances, accounts, investments, property, business and all other`
  line `administrative affairs of the University, and for that purpose, to appoint such agents as it may think`
  line fit;
  line
  line `(f) to invest any money belonging to the University, including any unapplied income, in such`
  line `stocks, funds, shares or securities as it thinks fit, or in the purchase of immovable property in India;`
  line
  line `(g) to exercise such other powers and perform such other functions as may be conferred or`
  line `specified by this Act or the Statutes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (41277)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `The Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41277&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council) shall be`
  line `^1[the principal academic body] of the University, and shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `Statutes and the Ordinances, have the control and general regulation, and be responsible for the`
  line `maintenance of standards of ^2[learning, education, instruction, evaluation and examination] within the`
  line `University, and shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or`
  line `imposed upon it by the Statutes and shall have the right to advise the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council)`
  line `on all academic matters.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution of the Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council) and the terms of office of its members`
  line `shall be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 15, for "the academic body" (w..f. 8-8-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "instruction, education and examination" (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (41278)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Other authorities of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for section 25 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41278&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Other authorities of the University.--The constitution, powers and functions of the`
  line `Artha-Samiti (Finance Committee), the Institute Board and of such other authorities as may be declared`
  line `by the Statutes to be authorities of the University shall be such as may be prescribed by the Statutes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (41279)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Alumni Association.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41279&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The University shall have an Alumni Association open to past students`
  line `and past workers of the University, including members of the Asramika Sangha of the former VisvaBharati Society, on such conditions as may be laid down in the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (41280)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title Statutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for section 27 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41280&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[27. Statutes.--Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of appointment, of the Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor), the term of his`
  line `appointments, emoluments and other conditions of his service;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers that may be exercised and the functions that may be performed by the Upacharya`
  line `(Vice-Chancellor);`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of appointment of the Karma-Sachiva (Registrar), the emoluments and other`
  line `conditions of his service and the powers that may be exercised and the functions that may be`
  line `performed by him;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of appointment of all other officers, the terms of their appointment, emoluments`
  line `and other conditions of their service and the powers and functions of such officers;`
  line
  line `(e) the constitution of the Samsad (Court), the term of office of its members and its powers and`
  line functions;
  line
  line `(f) the constitution of the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council), the term of office of its members`
  line `and its powers and functions;`
  line
  line `(g) the constitution of other authorities or bodies of the University, the term of office of their`
  line `members and their powers and functions;`
  line
  line `(h) the election and continuance in office of the members the said authorities and bodies, the`
  line `filling up of vacancies of members and all other matters relating to those authorities and other bodies`
  line `for which it may be necessary or desirable to provide;`
  line
  line `(i) the appointment of adhyapakas and other academic staff and other employees of the`
  line `University and their emoluments and other conditions of service:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any person who had held any post and is in receipt of a pension or other form of`
  line `retirement benefits is appointed as an adhyapaka of the University or to any other academic post, the`
  line `salary of such person together with the pension and other benefits shall not exceed the salary payable to`
  line `him in accordance with the Statutes;`
  line
  line `(j) the appointment of adhyapakas and other academic staff working in any other University,`
  line `institution or organisation for a specified period for undertaking a joint project;`
  line
  line `(k) the appointment of Visiting Professors, Emeritus Professors, Fellows, Scholars, Resident Artists`
  line `and Resident Writers, and terms and conditions of such appointment;`
  line
  line `(l) the constitution of a pension or provident fund or the establishment of an insurance scheme for the`
  line `benefit of the employees of the University;`
  line
  line `(m) the principles governing seniority of service of the employees of the University;`
  line
  line `(n) the procedure in relation to any appeal or application for review by any employee or student of the`
  line `University, against the action of any officer or authority of the University, including the time within`
  line `which such appeal or application for review may be preferred or made;`
  line
  line `(o) the procedure for the settlement of disputes between employees of the University, or students of`
  line `the University, and the University;`
  line
  line `(p) the conferment of honorary degrees;`
  line
  line `(q) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(r) the maintenance of discipline among the employees and students of the University;`
  line
  line `(s) the establishment and abolition of Bhavanas, Departments, Chatravasas and other institutions and`
  line `their management, supervision and inspection;`
  line
  line `(t) the regulation of the conduct and duties of the employees of the University and the conduct of the`
  line `students of the University;`
  line
  line `(u) the establishment of campuses, special centres, specialised laboratories or other units for research`
  line `and instruction;`
  line
  line `(v) the administration and regulation of the funds received in trust or otherwise by the University;`
  line
  line `(w) the delegation of powers vested in the officers or authorities of the University;`
  line
  line `(x) the constitution and activities of the Alumni Association;`
  line
  line `(y) the categories of misconduct for which any action may be taken under this Act, or the Statutes or`
  line `the Ordinances; and`
  line
  line `(z) all other matters which, by this Act, are to be, or may be, provided for by the Statutes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (41281)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Statutes, how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41281&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) On the commencement of the Visva-Bharati (Amendment) Act, 1984`
  line `(31 of 1984), the Statutes in force immediately before such commencement, as amended by that Act, shall`
  line `be the Statutes of the University.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Statutes may be amended, repealed or added to by Statutes made by the Karma Samiti`
  line `(Executive Council).`
  line
  line `(3) The Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall not propose the draft of any Statute affecting the`
  line `status, powers or constitution of any authority of the University until such authority has been given an`
  line `opportunity of expressing the opinion upon the proposal and any opinion so expressed shall be in writing`
  line `and shall be submitted to the Paridarsaka (Visitor).`
  line
  line `(4) Every new Statute or addition to a Statute or any amendment or repeal of a Statute shall be`
  line `submitted to the Paridarsaka (Visitor) who may assent to it or withhold his assent therefrom or remit it to`
  line `the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) for further consideration.`
  line
  line `(5) A Statute passed by the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall have no validity until it has been`
  line `assented to by the Paridarsaka (Visitor).]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 18, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 57 of 1971, s. 7, for sub-sections (2) to (8) (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (41282)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Matters to be provided for in the Ordinances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 19, for sections 29 and 30 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41282&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `^1[29. Matters to be provided for in the Ordinances.--Subject to the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `Statutes, the Ordinances may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of students to the University and their enrolment as such;`
  line
  line `(b) the pattern of learning process, courses of study to be laid down for all degrees, diplomas and`
  line `certificates of the University;`
  line
  line `(c) the degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions to be awarded by the`
  line `University, the qualifications for the same and the means to be adopted relating to the granting and`
  line `obtaining of the same;`
  line
  line `(d) the purposes for which certificates awarded by the Lok Siksha-Samsad (People's Education`
  line `Council) of the University may be recognised by the University;`
  line
  line `(e) the fees to be charged for courses of study in the University and for admission to the`
  line `examinations, and processes of evaluation, degrees, diplomas and certificates of the University;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions of the award of fellowships, scholarships, studentships, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(g) the conduct of tests, evaluations and examinations, including the terms of office and manner`
  line `of appointment and duties of examining bodies, examiners, moderators and persons entrusted with the`
  line `responsibility of evaluation;`
  line
  line `(h) the conditions of residence of the students of the University and the special arrangements, if`
  line `any, for the residence of women students;`
  line
  line `(i) the special arrangements, if any, which may be made for the discipline and teaching of women`
  line `students, and prescribing for them special courses of study;`
  line
  line `(j) the terms and conditions of service of the employees of the University other than those`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes (including the emoluments of the non-teaching staff):`
  line
  line `Provided that where any person who had held any post and is in receipt of a pension or other form`
  line `of retirement benefits is appointed to a non-teaching post of the University, the salary of such person`
  line `together with the pension and other benefits shall not exceed the salary payable to him in accordance`
  line `with the Ordinances;`
  line
  line `(k) the terms and conditions of approval of institutions of higher learning and its withdrawal;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of co-operation or collaboration or association with other Universities, authorities`
  line `or institutions of learning;`
  line
  line `(m) the terms and conditions on which persons working in an approved institution, or in any`
  line `institution co-operating, collaborating or associating with the University, may be approved as`
  line `adhyapakas and for withdrawing such approval;`
  line
  line `(n) the educational experimentation and the creation, composition and functioning of any other`
  line `body which is considered necessary for improving the academic life of the University; and`
  line
  line `(o) all other matters which, by this Act or the Statutes, are to be, or may be, provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.]
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (41283)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to make Ordinances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 19, for sections 29 and 30 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41283&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[30. Power to make Ordinances.--(1) The Ordinances in force immediately before the`
  line `commencement of the Visva-Bharati (Amendment) Act, 1984 (31 of 1984), may be amended, repealed or`
  line `added to, at any time by the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council):`
  line
  line `Provided that no Ordinance shall be made in respect of matters enumerated in section 29, other than`
  line `those enumerated in clauses (e), (h), (j), (m) and (o) thereof, unless a draft of such Ordinance has been`
  line `proposed by the Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council).`
  line
  line `(2) The Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall not have power to amend any draft proposed by the`
  line `Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council) under the provisions of sub-section (1), but may reject the proposal or`
  line `return the draft to the Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council) for reconsideration either in whole or in part,`
  line `together with any amendments which the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) may suggest.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) has rejected or returned the draft of an Ordinance`
  line `proposed by the Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council), the Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council) may consider`
  line `the question afresh and in case the original draft is reaffirmed by a majority of not less than one-half of`
  line `the total membership of the Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council) and by a majority of not less than twothirds of the members of the Siksha-Samiti (Academic Council) present and voting, the draft may be sent`
  line `back to the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council), which shall either adopt it or refer it to the Paridarsaka`
  line `(Visitor) whose decision thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Every Ordinance made by the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall come into effect`
  line immediately.
  line
  line `(5) Every Ordinance made by the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall be submitted to the`
  line `Paridarsaka (Visitor) within four weeks of the date of the meeting of the Karma-Samiti (Executive`
  line `Council), and the Paridarsaka (Visitor) shall have the power to direct the University, within six weeks`
  line `from the date of the receipt of the Ordinance, to suspend the operation of any Ordinance and he shall, as`
  line `soon as possible, inform the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) about his objection to the proposed`
  line Ordinance.
  line
  line `(6) The Paridarsaka (Visitor) may, after receiving the comments of the University, either withdraw`
  line `the order directing the suspension of the Ordinance or disallow the Ordinance and his decision thereon`
  line `shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (41284)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title Regulations.
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41284&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The authorities of the University may make Regulations consistent with this`
  line `Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances--`
  line
  line `(a) laying down the procedure to be observed at their meetings and the number of members`
  line `required to form a quorum;`
  line
  line `(b) providing for all matters which by this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances are to be prescribed`
  line `by the Regulations; and`
  line
  line `(c) providing for all other matters solely concerning the authorities or committees appointed by`
  line `them and not provided for by this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(2) Every authority of the University shall make Regulations providing for the giving of notice to the`
  line `members of such authority of the dates of meetings and of the business to be considered at meetings and`
  line `for the keeping of a record of the proceedings of meetings.`
  line
  line `(3) The Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) may direct the amendment, in such manner as it may`
  line `specify, of any Regulation made under this section or the amendment of any Regulation made under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `^1[(4) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be published in the Official`
  line Gazette.
  line
  line `(5) Every Statute, Ordinance or Regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days, which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation or both Houses agree that the Statute,`
  line `Ordinance or Regulation should not be made, the Statute, Ordinance or Regulation shall thereafter have`
  line `effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that Statute, Ordinance or Regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (41285)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title Residence.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41285&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every student of the University ^1[other than a student of its Lok Siksha Samsad`
  line `(People's Education Council)] shall reside in a ^2[Chatravasa] or under such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes and the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 60 of 1961, s. 13 (w.e.f. 19-12-1961).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 20, for "Bhavana (College) or Chartavasa (Hostel)" (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (41286)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title Admission.
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41286&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Admission of students to the University shall be made in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (41287)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title Examinations.
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for "examinations" (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41287&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of the Statutes, all arrangements for the conduct of`
  line `^1[tests, evaluations and examinations] shall be made by the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Ordinances.`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (41288)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s.22, ibid., for sections 35 and 36 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41288&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `^1[35. Annual report.--(1) The annual report of the University shall be prepared under the directions`
  line `of the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) which shall include, among other matters, the steps taken by the`
  line `University to promote socially relevant research in physical and social sciences, weaker sections' need`
  line `oriented extension activities and integration of the community life of the University with that of the wider`
  line world.
  line
  line `(2) The annual report so prepared shall be submitted to the Samsad (Court) on or before such date as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Statutes and shall be considered by the Samsad (Court) in its annual meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The Samsad (Court) may communicate its comments on the annual report to the Karma-Samiti`
  line `(Executive Council) and the Paridarsaka (Visitor).`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of the annual report, as prepared under sub-section (1) shall also be submitted to the`
  line `Central Government which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be laid before both the Houses of`
  line Parliament.]
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (41289)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Annual Accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s.22, ibid., for sections 35 and 36 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41289&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `^1[36. Annual Accounts.--(1) The annual accounts and balance-sheet of the University shall be`
  line `prepared under the direction of the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) and shall once at least every year`
  line `and at intervals of not more than fifteen months, be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line `India or by such person or persons as he may authorise in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the accounts together with the audit report shall be submitted to the Samsad (Court) and`
  line `the Paridarsaka (Visitor) along with the observations of the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council).`
  line
  line `(3) Any observations made by the Paridarsaka (Visitor) on the annual accounts shall be brought to`
  line `the notice of the Samsad (Court) and the observations of the Samsad (Court), if any, shall, after being`
  line `considered by the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council), be submitted to the Paridarsaka (Visitor).`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of the accounts together with the audit report, as submitted to the Paridarsaka (Visitor),`
  line `shall also be submitted to the Central Government, which shall, as soon as may be, cause the same to be`
  line `laid before both the Houses of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(5) The audited annual accounts, after having been laid before both the Houses of Parliament, shall be`
  line `published in the Gazette of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (41290)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Adhyapakas of the University to be appointed under a written contract.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 23, for sections 37 and 38 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41290&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1[37. Adhyapakas of the University to be appointed under a written contract.--(1) No`
  line `adhyapaka of the University shall be appointed to a permanent post, except under a written contract and`
  line `such contract shall not be inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(2) The contract referred to in sub-section (1) shall be lodged with the University and a copy thereof`
  line `shall be furnished to the adhyapaka concerned.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of an adhyapaka appointed by the University before the commencement of the Visva-Bharati (Amendment) Act, 1984 (31 of 1984), the contract in force immediately before such`
  line `commencement, in relation to his emoluments, shall, to the extent of any inconsistency with the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the Statutes or the Ordinances, be deemed to have been modified by the said`
  line `provisions and where there is no such contract and the adhyapaka is a salaries adhyapaka appointed to a`
  line `permanent post, a written contract shall be executed by, and between, such adhyapaka and the University`
  line `within a period of six months from the commencement of the Visva-Bharati (Amendment) Act, 1984.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (41291)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 23, for sections 37 and 38 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41291&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `^1[38. Tribunal of Arbitration.--(1) Any dispute arising out of a contract of employment referred to in`
  line `section 37, including a dispute relating to the non-compliance of the provisions of this Act, the Statutes or`
  line `the Ordinances, shall, at the request of the adhyapaka, be referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration which shall`
  line `consist of one member nominated by the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council), one member nominated by`
  line `the adhyapaka concerned and one member (who shall act as umpire) nominated by the Paridarsaka`
  line `(Visitor).`
  line
  line `(2) Every request made under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be a submission to arbitration upon`
  line `the terms of this section within the meaning of the Arbitration Act, 1940 (10 of 1940), and all the`
  line `provisions of that Act, with the exception of section 2 thereof, shall apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) If, for any reason, a vacancy occurs in the office of a member of the Tribunal of Arbitration, the`
  line `appropriate body or person concerned shall nominate another person in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) to fill the vacancy and the proceedings may be continued before the Tribunal from the`
  line `stage at which the vacancy is filled.`
  line
  line `(4) The decision of the Tribunal of Arbitration shall be final and binding on the parties.`
  line
  line `(5) The Tribunal of Arbitration shall have the power--`
  line
  line `(a) to regulate its own procedure;`
  line
  line `(b) to order reinstatement of the adhyapaka concerned; and`
  line
  line `(c) to award salary to the adhyapaka concerned, after deducting therefrom such income, not being`
  line `income from property, as such adhyapaka might have derived during the period of his suspension or`
  line `during the period intervening between the date on which he was removed or dismissed from service`
  line `or, as the case may be, his service was terminated, and the date on which he is reinstated:`
  line
  line `Provided that the income which could have been derived by the adhyapaka concerned shall not`
  line `be taken into account if, at the time when the income was derived, he could have derived such income`
  line `had he not been suspended or removed or dismissed from service or if his service had not been`
  line terminated.
  line
  line `(6) No suit or other proceedings shall lie in any court in respect of any matter which is required by`
  line `sub-section (1) to be referred to the Tribunal of Arbitration.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_a:
  sectionId (41292)
  sectionNo 38A
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to suspend adhyapaka or other member of academic staff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 23, for sections 37 and 38 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41292&sectionno=38A&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[38A. Power to suspend adhyapaka or other member of academic staff.--(1) The Upacharya`
  line `(Vice-Chancellor) may, by order in writing, place and adhyapaka or other member of the academic staff`
  line `under suspension--`
  line
  line `(a) where a disciplinary proceeding against such adhyapaka or other member is contemplated or`
  line `is pending; or`
  line
  line `(b) where a case against him in respect of any criminal offence is under investigation or trial.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any order of suspension is made under sub-section (1), the circumstances in which such`
  line `order has been made shall be reported forthwith to the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council).`
  line
  line `(3) The Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) may, within fifteen days from the date of receipt of the`
  line `report referred to in sub-section (2), revoke the order of suspension if it is of opinion that the`
  line `circumstances of the case do not warrant the suspension.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by an order of suspension, which has not been revoked under sub-section`
  line `(3), may prefer an appeal to the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) within thirty days from the date on`
  line `which such order is communicated to him and the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) may confirm`
  line `modify or reverse the order appealed against.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_b:
  sectionId (41305)
  sectionNo 38B
  orderNo 40
  title `Authorities by whom order for removal or dismissal or adhyapaka, etc., may be made and the procedure therefor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_b_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 23, for sections 37 and 38 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41305&sectionno=38B&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_38_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[38B. Authorities by whom order for removal or dismissal of adhyapaka, etc., may be made and`
  line `the procedure therefor.--(1) No adhyapaka, or other member of the academic staff, appointed by the`
  line `University shall be dismissed or removed from service or punished in any other manner by any authority`
  line `other than the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council).`
  line
  line `(2) No adhyapaka, or other member of the academic staff, appointed by the University shall be`
  line `dismissed or removed from service or punished in any other manner except after an inquiry in which he`
  line `has been informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in`
  line `respect of those charges:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is proposed after such inquiry, to impose upon the adhyapaka or other member`
  line `of the academic staff any punishment, such punishment may be imposed on the basis of the evidence`
  line `adduced during such inquiry and it shall not be necessary to give such adhyapaka or other member of the`
  line `academic staff any opportunity of making representation on the punishment proposed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) shall be entitled to dismiss or remove from service,`
  line `without holding any such inquiry as is referred to in sub-section (2), an adhyapaka, or other member of`
  line `the academic staff, of the University, where the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council), for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, is satisfied that such adhyapaka or other member of the academic staff--`
  line
  line `(a) is of unsound mind or is a deaf-mute or suffers from contagious leprosy; or`
  line
  line `(b) is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(c) has been convicted, by a court of law, of an offence involving moral turpitude.`
  line
  line `(4) The dismissal or removal from service of, or any other punishment imposed on, an adhyapaka, or`
  line `other member of the academic staff, appointed by the University shall take effect from the date on which`
  line `the order of dismissal or removal from service is made or other punishment is imposed:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the adhyapaka or other member of the academic staff is under suspension at the`
  line `time when the order for his dismissal or removal from service is made or other punishment is imposed,`
  line `such order may, if the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) so directs, take effect from the date on which he`
  line `was placed under suspension.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding the terms of contract between the University and an adhyapaka, or other member`
  line `of the academic staff, appointed by the University, such adhyapaka or other member of the academic staff`
  line `may resign his office--`
  line
  line `(a) where he is permanent, by giving three months' notice in writing to the Karma-Samiti`
  line `(Executive Council) or by paying to the University three months' salary in lieu of such notice; or`
  line
  line `(b) where he is not permanent, one month's notice in writing to the Karma-Samiti (Executive`
  line `Council) or by paying to the University one month's salary in lieu of such notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council) so permits, the period of three months'`
  line `notice or of one month's notice, as the case may be, may be reduced or waived:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such resignation shall take effect from the date on which it is accepted by`
  line `the Karma-Samiti (Executive Council).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--"Suspension" shall not be deemed to be a punishment within the meaning of this`
  line section.]
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (41294)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Pension and provident funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 2, for "teacher" (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41294&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The University shall constitute, for the benefit of its officers`
  line `[including the Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor)], ^1[adhyapakas], and other servants, in such manner and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Statutes, such pension, insurance and provident`
  line `funds as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any such pension, insurance or provident fund has been so constituted, the Central`
  line `Government may declare that the provisions of the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (17 of 1925), shall apply to`
  line `such fund as if it were a Government Provident Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (41295)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `Filling of casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 60 of 1961, s. 15, for "till the next meeting of the Samsad (Court)" (w.e.f. 19-12-1961).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41295&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any provision in this Act and in the Statutes, the`
  line `Karma Samiti (Executive Council) shall appoint, with the approval of the Paridarsaka (Visitor), a person`
  line `to fill a casual vacancy in the office of the Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor), and the person so appointed`
  line `shall hold office ^1[until his successor enters upon his office].`
  line
  line `(2) All casual vacancies among the members (other than ex officio members) of any authority or other`
  line `body of the University shall be filled, as soon as conveniently may be, by the person or body who`
  line `appointed, elected or co-opted the member whose place has become vacant, and the person appointed,`
  line `clected or co-opted to a casual vacancy shall be member of such authority or body for the residue of the`
  line `term for which the person whose place he fills would have been a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (41296)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Removal from membership of the University.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 57 of 1971, s. 11, for section 41 (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41296&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `^1[41. Removal from membership of the University.--The Karma Samiti (Executive Council) may,`
  line `on the recommendation of not less than two-thirds of its members remove any person from the`
  line `membership of any authority or board of the University if such a person is guilty of a serious offence`
  line `involving moral turpitude, or if he has been guilty of scandalous conduct and for the same reasons may`
  line `withdraw any degree or diploma conferred on, or granted to, any person by the University:`
  line
  line `Provided that no action shall be taken under this section against any person except after giving him a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard with regard to the proposed action.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (41297)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Disputes as to constitution of any University authority or body.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41297&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `If any question arises`
  line `whether any person has been duly elected or appointed as, or is entitled to be, a member of any authority`
  line `or other body of the University, the matter shall be referred to the Paridarsaka (Visitor), whose decision`
  line `thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (41298)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title `Constitution of committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41298&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Where any authority of the University is given power by this Act`
  line `or by the Statutes to appoint committees, such committee shall, unless there is some special provision to`
  line `the contrary, consist of members of the authority concerned and of such other persons (if any) as the`
  line `authority in each case may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (41299)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 46
  title `Proceedings of the University authorities not invalidated by vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41299&sectionno=44&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding`
  line `of any authority or other body of the University shall be invalidated merely by reason of the existence of a`
  line `vacancy or vacancies among its members.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44_a:
  sectionId (41300)
  sectionNo 44A
  orderNo 47
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 24 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41300&sectionno=44A&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_44_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[44A. Protection of action taken in good faith.--No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against`
  line `any officer or employee of the University for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done,`
  line `in pursuance of the provisions of this Act, the Statutes or the Ordinances.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44_b:
  sectionId (41301)
  sectionNo 44B
  orderNo 48
  title `Mode of proof of University record.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1984, s. 24 (w.e.f. 8-8-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41301&sectionno=44B&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_44_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[44B. Mode of proof of University record.--A copy of any receipt, application, notice, order,`
  line `proceeding or resolution of any authority or committee of the University, or other documents in the`
  line `possession of the University, or any entry in any register duly maintained by the University, if certified by`
  line `the Karma-Sachiva (Registrar), shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act,`
  line `1872 (1 of 1872), or in any other law for the time being in force, be admitted as evidence of the matters`
  line `and transactions specified therein where the original thereof would, if produced, have been admissible in`
  line evidence.]
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (41302)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 49
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189&sectionId=41302&sectionno=45&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00005_195129_1517807321189
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises with respect to the establishment of the`
  line `University or any authority of the University or in connection with the first meeting of any authority of`
  line `the University, the Paridarsaka (Visitor) in consultation with the Upacharya (Vice-Chancellor) may, by`
  line `order, make any appointment or do anything which appears to him necessary or expedient for the proper`
  line `establishment of the University or any authority thereof or for the first meeting of any authority of the`
  line University.
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
